# Downloaded source data + generated outputs
data/*
*.csv

# ...but DO commit the small illustrative result samples
!data_samples/
!data_samples/*.csv

# ...and DO commit the static monthly macro series (fixed historical record, pulled once).
# Note: ignore data/* (contents) not data/ (dir) so this un-ignore can take effect.
!data/macro_monthly.csv

# ...and the generated feature-importance table (small, handy to diff across runs)
!feature_importance.csv

# ...and DO commit the FROZEN historical poll snapshots (Internet Archive captures of 538,
# which never change). Committing them removes the fragile/rate-limited live Wayback dependency.
# Current-cycle NYT files (*_current.csv) and result files stay ignored (they refresh / are on live GitHub).
!data/senate_historical.csv
!data/house_historical.csv
!data/governor_historical.csv
!data/generic_ballot_historical.csv

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.env
